 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWell.\r\n\r\n468\r\n00:26:42,280 --> 00:26:44,168  X1:288 X2:434 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Thank you.\r\n- Thank you.\r\n\r\n469\r\n00:26:44,234 --> 00:26:46,951  X1:152 X2:569 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYou\'re a wonderful tennis player...\r\n\r\n470\r\n00:26:47,018 --> 00:26:49,441  X1:194 X2:528 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nand you\'re the worst driver\r\nl\'ve ever seen in my life.\r\n\r\n471\r\n00:26:49,514 --> 00:26:53,127  X1:154 X2:568 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAnyplace. Europe. Anyplace. Asia.\r\n\r\n472\r\n00:26:53,195 --> 00:26:55,465  X1:190 X2:532 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l love what you\'re wearing.\r\n- You do? Yeah.\r\n\r\n473\r\n00:26:55,532 --> 00:27:01,72  X1:125 X2:597 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThis tie is a present from Grammy Hall.\r\n\r\n474\r\n00:27:01,78 --> 00:27:02,179  X1:237 X2:485 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWho? Grammy Hall?\r\n\r\n475\r\n00:27:02,254 --> 00:27:03,880  X1:248 X2:474 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYeah, my grammy.\r\n\r\n476\r\n00:27:03,951 --> 00:27:06,985  X1:099 X2:622 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat did you do, grow up in a\r\nNorman Rockwell painting? Your grammy?\r\n\r\n477\r\n00:27:07,055 --> 00:27:11,180  X1:173 X2:548 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- lt\'s pretty silly, isn\'t it?\r\n- My grammy never gave gifts.\r\n\r\n478\r\n00:27:11,248 --> 00:27:14,064  X1:167 X2:555 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nShe was too busy getting raped\r\nby Cossacks.\r\n\r\n479\r\n00:27:14,129 --> 00:27:16,268  X1:230 X2:492 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWell, thank you again.\r\n\r\n480\r\n00:27:16,337 --> 00:27:17,832  X1:305 X2:417 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nOh, yeah.\r\n\r\n481\r\n00:27:17,906 --> 00:27:21,616  X1:120 X2:602 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nListen. You want to come upstairs\r\nand have a glass of wine or something?\r\n\r\n482\r\n00:27:21,684 --> 00:27:25,001  X1:139 X2:583 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo, l mean you don\'t have to.\r\nYou\'re probably late and everything.\r\n\r\n483\r\n00:27:25,077 --> 00:27:27,314  X1:224 X2:497 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo, that would be fine.\r\nl wouldn\'t mind. Sure.\r\n\r\n484\r\n00:27:27,381 --> 00:27:31,823  X1:180 X2:541 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl got time. l got nothing\r\nuntil my analyst appointment.\r\n\r\n485\r\n00:27:31,894 --> 00:27:33,870  X1:237 X2:484 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYou see an analyst?\r\n\r\n486\r\n00:27:33,943 --> 00:27:37,522  X1:243 X2:478 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Just for 15 years.\r\n- 15 years?\r\n\r\n487\r\n00:27:37,592 --> 00:27:40,014  X1:145 X2:576 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl\'m going to give him one more year,\r\nand then l\'m going to Lourdes.\r\n\r\n488\r\n00:27:40,088 --> 00:27:42,958  X1:160 X2:561 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\n15? Nah, come on! Yeah? Really?\r\n\r\n489\r\n00:27:43,129 --> 00:27:46,359  X1:162 X2:559 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nSylvia Plath. lnteresting poetess\r\nwhose tragic suicide...\r\n\r\n490\r\n00:27:46,426 --> 00:27:50,071  X1:163 X2:559 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nwas misinterpreted as romantic\r\nby the college-girl mentality.\r\n\r\n491\r\n00:27:51,067 --> 00:27:54,581  X1:129 X2:593 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nRight. l don\'t know.\r\nl mean, some of her poems seem neat.\r\n\r\n492\r\n00:27:54,652 --> 00:27:57,849  X1:147 X2:575 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nNeat? l hate to tell you this is 1975.\r\n\r\n493\r\n00:27:57,917 --> 00:28:00,220  X1:201 X2:520 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n\"Neat\" went out\r\nat the turn of the century.\r\n\r\n494\r\n00:28:00,286 --> 00:28:02,490  X1:150 X2:571 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWho are those photos on the wall?\r\n\r\n495\r\n00:28:02,558 --> 00:28:05,145  X1:282 X2:439 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nOh, you see...\r\n\r\n496\r\n00:28:05,215 --> 00:28:09,144  X1:180 X2:541 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nthat\'s my dad, that\'s Father,\r\nand that\'s my brother, Duane.\r\n\r\n497\r\n00:28:09,216 --> 00:28:11,999  X1:175 X2:546 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYeah, right.\r\nAnd over there\'s Grammy Hall.\r\n\r\n498\r\n00:28:12,065 --> 00:28:14,881  X1:248 X2:473 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- And that\'s Sadie.\r\n- Who\'s Sadie?\r\n\r\n499\r\n00:28:14,946 --> 00:28:20,414  X1:141 X2:580 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWell, Sadie met Grammy\r\nthrough Grammy\'s brother, George.\r\n\r\n500\r\n00:28:20,483 --> 00:28:22,720  X1:214 X2:508 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nGeorge was real sweet.\r\nHe had that thing.\r\n\r\n501\r\n00:28:22,788 --> 00:28:28,005  X1:119 X2:603 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat is that thing where you fall asleep\r\nin the middle of a sentence?\r\n\r\n502\r\n00:28:28,069 --> 00:28:29,924  X1:279 X2:443 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Narcolepsy.\r\n- Right.\r\n\r\n503\r\n00:28:29,990 --> 00:28:34,595  X1:135 X2:587 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nSo anyway, George went to the union\r\nto get his free turkey...\r\n\r\n504\r\n00:28:34,663 --> 00:28:38,177  X1:123 X2:599 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nbecause the union always gave George\r\nthis free turkey at Christmastime...\r\n\r\n505\r\n00:28:38,248 --> 00:28:41,632  X1:177 X2:545 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nbecause he was shell-shocked\r\nin the first World War.\r\n\r\n506\r\n00:28:41,704 --> 00:28:45,535  X1:128 X2:594 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAnyway, so George is standing in line...\r\n\r\n507\r\n00:28:45,610 --> 00:28:47,912  X1:212 X2:509 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\ngetting his free turkey...\r\n\r\n508\r\n00:28:47,978 --> 00:28:52,835  X1:176 X2:546 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nbut the thing is he falls asleep,\r\nand he never wakes up.\r\n\r\n509\r\n00:28:52,908 --> 00:28:55,495  X1:281 X2:440 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nSo he\'s dead.\r\n\r\n510\r\n00:28:55,564 --> 00:28:57,769  X1:261 X2:460 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nHe\'s dead. Yeah.\r\n\r\n511\r\n00:28:57,837 --> 00:28:59,299  X1:305 X2:416 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nOh, dear.\r\n\r\n512\r\n00:28:59,374 --> 00:29:02,025  X1:246 X2:475 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWell, terrible, huh?\r\nWouldn\'t you say?\r\n\r\n513\r\n00:29:02,094 --> 00:29:03,753  X1:278 X2:444 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nPretty awful.\r\n\r\n514\r\n00:29:03,823 --> 00:29:07,021  X1:205 X2:517 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt\'s a great story, though.\r\nlt really made my day.\r\n\r\n515\r\n00:29:07,088 --> 00:29:10,056  X1:179 X2:542 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl think l should get out of here,\r\n\'cause l think l\'m imposing.\r\n\r\n516\r\n00:29:10,129 --> 00:29:13,129  X1:261 X2:461 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nReally? Maybe--\r\n\r\n517\r\n00:29:13,201 --> 00:29:17,326  X1:135 X2:587 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- You do