:216 X2:506 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl\'ll never know when\r\nto make the right move.\r\n\r\n583\r\n00:33:19,444 --> 00:33:22,096  X1:152 X2:569 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWe\'ll kiss now and get it over with,\r\nand then we\'ll go eat. Okay?\r\n\r\n584\r\n00:33:22,165 --> 00:33:24,434  X1:189 X2:533 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWe\'ll digest our food better.\r\n\r\n585\r\n00:33:26,197 --> 00:33:29,178  X1:145 X2:577 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nOkay? Now we can digest our food.\r\n\r\n586\r\n00:33:29,306 --> 00:33:31,380  X1:233 X2:489 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nCorned beef, please.\r\n\r\n587\r\n00:33:31,451 --> 00:33:34,451  X1:138 X2:583 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl\'m having pastrami on white bread...\r\n\r\n588\r\n00:33:34,524 --> 00:33:37,372  X1:116 X2:605 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nwith mayonnaise, tomatoes and lettuce.\r\n\r\n589\r\n00:33:40,061 --> 00:33:42,997  X1:181 X2:541 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nSo, your second wife left you.\r\n\r\n590\r\n00:33:43,070 --> 00:33:45,623  X1:158 X2:563 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWere you depressed about that?\r\n\r\n591\r\n00:33:45,695 --> 00:33:49,177  X1:149 X2:572 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNothing that a few mega-vitamins\r\ncouldn\'t cure.\r\n\r\n592\r\n00:33:49,248 --> 00:33:52,958  X1:210 X2:511 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Your first wife, Allison.\r\n- She was nice.\r\n\r\n593\r\n00:33:53,024 --> 00:33:55,414  X1:245 X2:476 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThat was my fault.\r\nl was too crazy.\r\n\r\n594\r\n00:33:59,171 --> 00:34:02,685  X1:255 X2:466 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThat was so nice!\r\nThat was nice.\r\n\r\n595\r\n00:34:02,755 --> 00:34:06,466  X1:192 X2:530 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAs Balzac said,\r\n\"There goes another novel.\"\r\n\r\n596\r\n00:34:07,525 --> 00:34:09,184  X1:261 X2:461 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYou were great.\r\n\r\n597\r\n00:34:09,253 --> 00:34:11,709  X1:257 X2:465 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nOh, yeah? Yeah?\r\n\r\n598\r\n00:34:11,781 --> 00:34:15,776  X1:238 X2:483 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Yeah, l\'m wrecked.\r\n- You\'re wrecked.\r\n\r\n599\r\n00:34:15,847 --> 00:34:20,191  X1:183 X2:539 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl mean it.\r\nl\'ll never play the