\n\r\n1013\r\n00:58:01,61 --> 00:58:04,089  X1:150 X2:571 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl think we\'re both much too mature\r\nfor something like that.\r\n\r\n1014\r\n00:58:04,160 --> 00:58:06,878  X1:148 X2:574 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nLiving together hasn\'t been so bad,\r\nhas it?\r\n\r\n1015\r\n00:58:06,945 --> 00:58:10,012  X1:214 X2:508 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nFor me it\'s been terrific.\r\nYou know?\r\n\r\n1016\r\n00:58:10,081 --> 00:58:12,537  X1:141 X2:580 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nBetter than either of my marriages.\r\n\r\n1017\r\n00:58:12,610 --> 00:58:16,801  X1:121 X2:601 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThere\'s something different about you.\r\nl don\'t know what, but it\'s great.\r\n\r\n1018\r\n00:58:16,867 --> 00:58:22,270  X1:177 X2:545 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl think, if you let me,\r\nl could help you have more fun.\r\n\r\n1019\r\n00:58:22,341 --> 00:58:25,309  X1:229 X2:492 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl know it\'s hard. Yeah.\r\n\r\n1020\r\n00:58:25,382 --> 00:58:28,896  X1:147 X2:574 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWhat if we go away this weekend?\r\n\r\n1021\r\n00:58:28,967 --> 00:58:32,383  X1:141 X2:580 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhy don\'t we get Rob, and the three\r\nof us would drive into Brooklyn?\r\n\r\n1022\r\n00:58:32,456 --> 00:58:35,009  X1:115 X2:607 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWe could show you the old neighborhood.\r\nThat\'d be fun for you.\r\n\r\n1023\r\n00:58:35,081 --> 00:58:37,088  X1:266 X2:455 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYeah, l\'d love it.\r\n\r\n1024\r\n00:58:38,025 --> 00:58:40,197  X1:234 X2:488 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nGod, it\'s a great day!\r\n\r\n1025\r\n00:58:40,265 --> 00:58:43,878  X1:245 X2:477 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWatch the road!\r\nYou\'ll total the car!\r\n\r\n1026\r\n00:58:43,946 --> 00:58:45,987  X1:194 X2:527 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl\'ve never been to Brooklyn.\r\n\r\n1027\r\n00:58:46,060 --> 00:58:48,548  X1:133 X2:589 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l can\'t wait to see the neighborhood.\r\n- The neighborhood will be great.\r\n\r\n1028\r\n00:58:48,620 --> 00:58:51,719  X1:144 X2:578 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- We could show her the schoolyard.\r\n- l was a great athlete. Tell her.\r\n\r\n1029\r\n00:58:51,789 --> 00:58:54,342  X1:236 X2:486 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl was all-schoolyard.\r\n\r\n1030\r\n00:58:54,413 --> 00:58:57,448  X1:170 X2:552 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThey threw him a football once.\r\nHe tried to dribble it.\r\n\r\n1031\r\n00:58:57,518 --> 00:58:59,046  X1:259 X2:462 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl used to lose\r\nmy glasses a lot.\r\n\r\n1032\r\n00:58:59,118 --> 00:59:02,633  X1:200 X2:522 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nLook! That\'s my old house.\r\nThat\'s where l used to live.\r\n\r\n1033\r\n00:59:02,703 --> 00:59:04,078  X1:303 X2:418 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nHoly cow!\r\n\r\n1034\r\n00:59:05,200 --> 00:59:08,201  X1:119 X2:603 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re lucky. Where l used to live\r\nis now a pornographic equipment store.\r\n\r\n1035\r\n00:59:08,273 --> 00:59:10,412  X1:227 X2:495 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl had some very\r\ngood memories there.\r\n\r\n1036\r\n00:59:10,481 --> 00:59:13,449  X1:150 X2:572 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat good memories, your mother\r\nand father fighting all the time?\r\n\r\n1037\r\n00:59:13,522 --> 00:59:15,978  X1:143 X2:578 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAnd over the most ridiculous things.\r\n\r\n1038\r\n00:59:16,115 --> 00:59:18,538  X1:163 X2:558 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- You fired the cleaning woman?\r\n- She was stealing!\r\n\r\n1039\r\n00:59:18,613 --> 00:59:21,035  X1:160 X2:562 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nBut she\'s colored.\r\nThe colored have enough trouble!\r\n\r\n1040\r\n00:59:21,109 --> 00:59:23,531  X1:152 X2:569 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- She was going through my purse.\r\n- They\'re persecuted enough.\r\n\r\n1041\r\n00:59:23,606 --> 00:59:27,436  X1:169 X2:553 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Who\'s persecuting? She stole!\r\n- So? We can afford it.\r\n\r\n1042\r\n00:59:27,510 --> 00:59:30,707  X1:146 X2:575 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nHow can we afford it, on your pay?\r\nWhat if she steals more?\r\n\r\n1043\r\n00:59:30,775 --> 00:59:33,743  X1:138 X2:583 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nShe\'s a colored woman from Harlem.\r\nShe has no money.\r\n\r\n1044\r\n00:59:33,816 --> 00:59:37,592  X1:122 X2:599 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nShe has a right to steal from us.\r\nWho can she steal from if not from us?\r\n\r\n1045\r\n00:59:37,657 --> 00:59:40,178  X1:231 X2:491 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- You\'re both crazy.\r\n- They can\'t hear you.\r\n\r\n1046\r\n00:59:40,250 --> 00:59:42,836  X1:236 X2:485 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nLeo, l married a fool!\r\n\r\n1047\r\n00:59:42,907 --> 00:59:44,663  X1:279 X2:443 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWhat\'s that?\r\n\r\n1048\r\n00:59:44,731 --> 00:59:49,948  X1:125 X2:596 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThat\'s the welcome home party, 1945,\r\nfor my cousin Herbie.\r\n\r\n1049\r\n00:59:52,574 --> 00:59:55,870  X1:229 X2:493 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nLook. That over there\r\nis Joey Nichols.\r\n\r\n1050\r\n00:59:55,934 --> 00:59:58,488  X1:130 X2:591 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nHe was my father\'s friend. He was\r\nalways bothering me when l was a kid.\r\n\r\n1051\r\n00:59:58,559 --> 01:00:01,374  X1:279 X2:442 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nJoey Nichols.\r\nSee? Nickels.\r\n\r\n1052\r\n01:00:01,439 --> 01:00:04,604  X1:254 X2:467 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nSee? Nickels.\r\nYou see? Nickels.\r\n\r\n1053\r\n01:00:04,672 --> 01:00:09,529  X1:139 X2:582 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou can always remember my name.\r\nJust think of Joey Five-Cents.\r\n\r\n1054\r\n01:00:09,602 --> 01:00:13,400  X1:258 X2:464 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThat\'s me.\r\nJoey Five-Cents.\r\n\r\n1055\r\n01:00:13,475 --> 01:00:15,002  X1:257 X2:465 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWhat an asshole.\r\n\r\n1056\r\n01:00:15,075 --> 01:00:18,272  X1:168 X2:554 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThe one who killed me the most\r\nwas my mother\'s sister, Tessie.\r\n\r\n1057\r\n01:00:18,340 --> 01:00:20,894  X1:199 X2:523 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl was always the sister\r\nwith good common sense...\r\n\r\n1058\r\n01:00:20,965 --> 01:00:23,519  X1:174 X2:547 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nbut Tessie was always the one\r\nwith personality.\r\n\r\n1059\r\n01:00:23,590 --> 01:00:26,460  X1:164 X2:557 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhen she was younger,\r\nthey all wanted to marry Tessie.\r\n\r\n1060\r\n01:00:26,535 --> 01:00:29,219  X1:231 X2:490 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nDo you believe Tessie\r\nhad the personality?\r\n\r\n1061\r\n01:00:29,287 --> 01:00:32,998  X1:131 X2:591 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- She\'s the life of the ghetto no doubt.\r\n- She was once a great beauty.\r\n\r\n1062\r\n01:00:33,064 --> 01:00:35,847  X1:141 X2:580 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nTessie, they say you were the sister\r\nwith personality.\r\n\r\n1063\r\n01:00:35,913 --> 01:00:38,401  X1:231 X2:490 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl was a great beauty!\r\n\r\n1064\r\n01:00:38,473 --> 01:00:42,336  X1:124 X2:597 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- How did this personality come about?\r\n- l was very charming.\r\n\r\n1065\r\n01:00:42,410 --> 01:00:44,483  X1:226 X2:496 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThere were many men\r\ninterested in you?\r\n\r\n1066\r\n01:00:44,555 --> 01:00:48,200  X1:202 X2:520 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl was quite a lively dancer.\r\n\r\n1067\r\n01:00:48,269 --> 01:00:50,156  X1:214 X2:507 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nlt\'s very hard to believe.\r\n\r\n1068\r\n01:00:50,252 --> 01:00:55,272  X1:123 X2:599 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl had a really good day.\r\nlt was a fine way to spend my birthday.\r\n\r\n1069\r\n01:00:55,343 --> 01:00:58,377  X1:143 X2:579 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Your birthday isn\'t until tomorrow.\r\n- But it\'s real close.\r\n\r\n1070\r\n01:00:58,447 --> 01:01:00,684  X1:177 X2:545 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nBut no presents until midnight.\r\n\r\n1071\r\n01:01:04,241 --> 01:01:05,616  X1:263 X2:458 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nHappy birthday.\r\n\r\n1072\r\n01:01:05,681 --> 01:01:08,682  X1:172 X2:550 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat is this? ls this a present?\r\nAre you kidding?\r\n\r\n1073\r\n01:01:08,753 --> 01:01:11,372  X1:181 X2:541 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYeah. Why don\'t you try it on?\r\n\r\n1074\r\n01:01:11,442 --> 01:01:15,786  X1:145 X2:577 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- This is more like a present for you.\r\n- lt\'ll add ten years to our sex life.\r\n\r\n1075\r\n01:01:15,860 --> 01:01:17,683  X1:266 X2:455 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYeah. Forget it.\r\n\r\n1076\r\n01:01:17,748 --> 01:01:20,334  X1:229 X2:493 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nHere\'s a real present.\