484 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNice. Santa Claus\r\nwill have sun stroke.\r\n\r\n1193\r\n01:09:26,154 --> 01:09:29,352  X1:227 X2:494 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nMax, there\'s no crime,\r\nthere\'s no mugging.\r\n\r\n1194\r\n01:09:29,387 --> 01:09:31,428  X1:191 X2:531 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThere\'s no economic crime...\r\n\r\n1195\r\n01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:34,534  X1:225 X2:497 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nbut there\'s ritual,\r\nreligious cult murders.\r\n\r\n1196\r\n01:09:34,605 --> 01:09:36,547  X1:234 X2:488 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThere\'s wheat-germ\r\nkillers out here.\r\n\r\n1197\r\n01:09:36,621 --> 01:09:39,142  X1:179 X2:542 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhile you\'re out here,\r\nl want you to see my TV show.\r\n\r\n1198\r\n01:09:39,213 --> 01:09:41,636  X1:207 X2:514 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAnd we\'re invited\r\nto a big Christmas party.\r\n\r\n1199\r\n01:09:52,305 --> 01:09:55,655  X1:150 X2:571 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nCharlie, give me a good laugh here.\r\n\r\n1200\r\n01:09:58,483 --> 01:10:00,425  X1:273 X2:448 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nA little bigger.\r\n\r\n1201\r\n01:10:00,500 --> 01:10:03,021  X1:195 X2:527 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nDo you realize how immoral\r\nthis all is?\r\n\r\n1202\r\n01:10:03,092 --> 01:10:05,133  X1:242 X2:479 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl\'ve got a hit series.\r\n\r\n1203\r\n01:10:05,205 --> 01:10:07,115  X1:177 X2:544 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nBut you\'re adding fake laughs.\r\n\r\n1204\r\n01:10:09,174 --> 01:10:11,990  X1:155 X2:566 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nGive me a tremendous laugh here.\r\n\r\n1205\r\n01:10:12,055 --> 01:10:14,062  X1:219 X2:502 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWe do the show live\r\nin front of an audience.\r\n\r\n1206\r\n01:10:14,135 --> 01:10:16,274  X1:168 X2:553 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nBut nobody laughs,\r\nbecause the jokes aren\'t funny.\r\n\r\n1207\r\n01:10:16,344 --> 01:10:18,800  X1:140 X2:582 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThat\'s why this machine is dynamite.\r\n\r\n1208\r\n01:10:22,585 --> 01:10:25,718  X1:164 X2:558 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nGive me a medium chuckle here...\r\n\r\n1209\r\n01:10:25,787 --> 01:10:28,657  X1:241 X2:481 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nand then a big hand.\r\n\r\n1210\r\n01:10:28,731 --> 01:10:31,482  X1:215 X2:506 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nls there booing on that?\r\n\r\n1211\r\n01:10:31,548 --> 01:10:34,167  X1:266 X2:456 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl don\'t feel well.\r\n\r\n1212\r\n01:10:34,237 --> 01:10:37,686  X1:230 X2:491 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- What\'s the matter?\r\n- l got very dizzy.\r\n\r\n1213\r\n01:10:37,757 --> 01:10:39,962  X1:283 X2:438 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l feel dizzy.\r\n- Sit down.\r\n\r\n1214\r\n01:10:40,030 --> 01:10:41,405  X1:321 X2:400 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nJesus.\r\n\r\n1215\r\n01:10:42,271 --> 01:10:45,119  X1:226 X2:496 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou all right?\r\nYou want to lie down?\r\n\r\n1216\r\n01:10:45,184 --> 01:10:48,086  X1:239 X2:483 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo. My stomach felt\r\nqueasy all morning.\r\n\r\n1217\r\n01:10:48,160 --> 01:10:50,168  X1:213 X2:509 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nHow about a ginger ale?\r\n\r\n1218\r\n01:10:50,241 --> 01:10:52,827  X1:206 X2:515 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo.\r\nMaybe l\'d better lie down.\r\n\r\n1219\r\n01:10:52,897 --> 01:10:56,510  X1:182 X2:539 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nTry to get some of this down.\r\nlt\'s just plain chicken.\r\n\r\n1220\r\n01:10:58,115 --> 01:11:00,963  X1:248 X2:473 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo, l can\'t eat this.\r\nl\'m nauseous.\r\n\r\n1221\r\n01:11:03,141 --> 01:11:06,720  X1:130 X2:591 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlf you could get me something\r\nto get me through the next two hours.\r\n\r\n1222\r\n01:11:06,790 --> 01:11:10,500  X1:140 X2:582 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl have to go to Burbank\r\nand give out an award on a TV show.\r\n\r\n1223\r\n01:11:10,567 --> 01:11:13,120  X1:170 X2:551 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThere\'s nothing wrong with you\r\nas far as l can tell.\r\n\r\n1224\r\n01:11:13,191 --> 01:11:16,258  X1:155 X2:566 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou have no fever,\r\nno symptoms of anything serious.\r\n\r\n1225\r\n01:11:16,328 --> 01:11:20,323  X1:137 X2:584 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- You haven\'t eaten pork or shellfish.\r\n- Excuse me. l\'m sorry, Doctor.\r\n\r\n1226\r\n01:11:20,393 --> 01:11:24,223  X1:141 X2:581 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAlvy, that was the show. Everything\r\nis fine. They found a replacement.\r\n\r\n1227\r\n01:11:24,298 --> 01:11:26,371  X1:153 X2:569 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThey\'re going to tape without you.\r\n\r\n1228\r\n01:11:26,443 --> 01:11:28,932  X1:149 X2:572 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nJesus!\r\nNow l don\'t get to do the TV show?\r\n\r\n1229\r\n01:11:30,507 --> 01:11:33,192  X1:167 X2:555 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l can\'t find any reason for this.\r\n- Nothing at all?\r\n\r\n1230\r\n01:11:33,261 --> 01:11:37,124  X1:179 X2:542 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l could get a lab man up here.\r\n- Hand me the salt, please.\r\n\r\n1231\r\n01:11:37,198 --> 01:11:41,093  X1:181 X2:541 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nPerhaps it would be better\r\nif we took him to the hospital.\r\n\r\n1232\r\n01:11:41,167 --> 01:11:42,541  X1:277 X2:445 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThe hospital?\r\n\r\n1233\r\n01:11:42,607 --> 01:11:45,781  X1:123 X2:598 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- There\'s no other way to diagnose him.\r\n- This is not bad, actually.\r\n\r\n1234\r\n01:11:50,775 --> 01:11:53,972  X1:148 X2:573 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nDon\'t tell me we\'re going to have\r\nto walk from the car to the house?\r\n\r\n1235\r\n01:11:54,039 --> 01:11:56,942  X1:147 X2:575 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nMy feet haven\'t touched pavement\r\nsince l reached Los Angeles.\r\n\r\n1236\r\n01:11:57,016 --> 01:12:00,661  X1:145 X2:576 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl\'ll take a meeting with you\r\nif you\'ll take a meeting with Freddy.\r\n\r\n1237\r\n01:12:00,729 --> 01:12:02,869  X1:145 X2:577 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl took a meeting with Freddy.\r\nFreddy took a meeting with Charlie.\r\n\r\n1238\r\n01:12:02,938 --> 01:12:05,524  X1:155 X2:566 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- You take a meeting with him.\r\n- All the good meetings are taken.\r\n\r\n1239\r\n01:12:05,594 --> 01:12:07,449  X1:197 X2:525 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nRight now it\'s only a notion.\r\n\r\n1240\r\n01:12:07,514 --> 01:12:11,444  X1:138 X2:583 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl think l can get money to make it into\r\na concept, then turn it into an idea.\r\n\r\n1241\r\n01:12:12,412 --> 01:12:14,135  X1:232 X2:490 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nLike this house, Max?\r\n\r\n1242\r\n01:12:14,205 --> 01:12:16,661  X1:201 X2:521 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nEven wrote a road map\r\nto get us to the bathroom.\r\n\r\n1243\r\n01:12:16,733 --> 01:12:18,708  X1:201 X2:521 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou should have told me\r\nit was Tony Lacey\'s party.\r\n\r\n1244\r\n01:12:18,781 --> 01:12:20,407  X1:151 X2:570 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWhat difference does that make?\r\n\r\n1245\r\n01:12:20,479 --> 01:12:22,334  X1:176 X2:546 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl think he has a thing for Annie.\r\n\r\n1246\r\n01:12:22,399 --> 01:12:26,197  X1:130 X2:592 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- No. He goes with that girl over there.\r\n- Where?\r\n\r\n1247\r\n01:12:26,272 --> 01:12:29,174  X1:222 X2:499 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- The one with the VPL.\r\n- VPL?\r\n\r\n1248\r\n01:12:29,249 --> 01:12:32,151  X1:255 X2:467 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nVisible panty line.\r\nShe\'s gorgeous.\r\n\r\n1249\r\n01:12:32,225 --> 01:12:35,292  X1:119 X2:602 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nShe\'s a ten. That\'s great for you,\r\n\'cause you\'re used to two\'s, aren\'t you?\r\n\r\n1250\r\n01:12:35,362 --> 01:12:36,889  X1:243 X2:479 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThere are no two\'s.\r\n\r\n1251\r\n01:12:36,963 --> 01:12:39,484  X1:135 X2:587 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re used to the kind with shopping\r\nbags walking through Central Park...\r\n\r\n1252\r\n01:12:39,555 --> 01:12:42,108  X1:195 X2:526 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nwith the surgical masks on,\r\nmuttering.\r\n\r\n1253\r\n01:12:42,180 --> 01:12:44,897  X1:124 X2:597 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nHow do you like this couple? They look\r\nlike they\'re from Masters and Johnson.\r\n\r\n1254\r\n01:12:44,964 --> 01:12:48,795  X1:235 X2:486 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlntensive care ward.\r\nMy God!\r\n\r\n1255\r\n01:12:48,870 --> 01:12:52,700  X1:126 X2:595 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l think she\'s giving me the eye.\r\n- lf she comes over, my brain will mush.\r\n\r\n1256\r\n01:12:53,992 --> 01:12:56,545  X1:203 X2:518 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re Alvy Singer, right?\r\nDidn\'t we meet at EST?\r\n\r\n1257\r\n01:12:56,616 --> 01:12:58,405  X1:223 X2:499 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nNo, l was never to EST.\r\n\r\n1258\r\n01:12:58,473 --> 01:13:01,440  X1:173 X2:548 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Then how can you criticize it?\r\n- He didn\'t say anything.\r\n\r\n1259\r\n01:13:01,513 --> 01:13:05,573  X1:152 X2:570 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl came to get some shock therapy,\r\nbut there was an energy crisis.\r\n\r\n1260\r\n01:13:05,643 --> 01:13:08,326  X1:108 X2:614 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- He\'s my food taster. Have you two met?\r\n- How do you do?\r\n\r\n1261\r\n01:13:08,395 --> 01:13:11,364  X1:154 X2:568 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Do you taste for poisoned food?\r\n- Yeah, he\'s great.\r\n\r\n1262\r\n01:13:11,437 --> 01:13:13,739  X1:188 X2:534 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou guys are wearing white.\r\nlt must be in the stars.\r\n\r\n1263\r\n01:13:13,805 --> 01:13:17,548  X1:142 X2:579 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Uri Geller must be on the premises.\r\n- We\'re going to operate together.\r\n\r\n1264\r\n01:13:17,613 --> 01:13:22,404  X1:181 X2:541 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nln about six weeks\r\nwe could cut the whole album.\r\n\r\n1265\r\n01:13:22,479 --> 01:13:24,781  X1:230 X2:491 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl don\'t know.\r\nThis is strange to me.\r\n\r\n1266\r\n01:13:24,848 --> 01:13:27,750  X1:165 X2:557 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou can stay here.\r\nUse the whole wing in this house.\r\n\r\n1267\r\n01:13:27,824 --> 01:13:32,266  X1:182 X2:539 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Stay here?\r\n- Really. Why are you smiling?\r\n\r\n1268\r\n01:13:32,337 --> 01:13:35,688  X1:167 X2:554 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNot only is he a great agent,\r\nbut he really gives good leading.\r\n\r\n1269\r\n01:13:35,762 --> 01:13:40,041  X1:180 X2:542 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThis is a great house: saunas,\r\nJacuzzis, three tennis courts.\r\n\r\n1270\r\n01:13:40,116 --> 01:13:44,208  X1:111 X2:611 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou know who the original owners were?\r\nNelson Eddy then Legs Diamond.\r\n\r\n1271\r\n01:13:44,277 --> 01:13:47,475  X1:165 X2:556 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Then you know who lived here?\r\n- Trigger.\r\n\r\n1272\r\n01:13:47,542 --> 01:13:50,804  X1:147 X2:575 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nCharlie Chaplin,\r\nright before his un-American thing.\r\n\r\n1273\r\n01:13:52,247 --> 01:13:56,274  X1:141 X2:580 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- But you guys are still New Yorkers.\r\n- Yeah, l love it there.\r\n\r\n1274\r\n01:13:56,344 --> 01:14:01,167  X1:185 X2:537 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl used to live there for years,\r\nbut it\'s so dirty now.\r\n\r\n1275\r\n01:14:01,242 --> 01:14:05,333  X1:172 X2:550 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l\'m into garbage. lt\'s my thing.\r\n- This is a nice screening room.\r\n\r\n1276\r\n01:14:05,403 --> 01:14:07,508  X1:125 X2:596 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThere\'s another thing about New York.\r\n\r\n1277\r\n01:14:07,580 --> 01:14:09,652  X1:198 X2:524 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlf you want to see a movie,\r\nyou have to stand on line.\r\n\r\n1278\r\n01:14:09,724 --> 01:14:11,993  X1:179 X2:542 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt could be freezing or raining.\r\nAnd here--\r\n\r\n1279\r\n01:14:12,061 --> 01:14:14,450  X1:135 X2:587 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWe saw Grand lllusion here last night.\r\n\r\n1280\r\n01:14:14,524 --> 01:14:17,373  X1:162 X2:559 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThat\'s a great film if you\'re high.\r\nlt\'s really funny.\r\n\r\n1281\r\n01:14:17,438 --> 01:14:20,570  X1:157 X2:564 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nCome and see our bedroom.\r\nWe did a fantastic thing up there.\r\n\r\n1282\r\n01:14:20,638 --> 01:14:22,646  X1:312 X2:409 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl\'m cool.\r\n\r\n1283\r\n01:14:22,719 --> 01:14:25,567  X1:149 X2:572 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt\'s wonderful.\r\nThey eat and watch movies all day.\r\n\r\n1284\r\n01:14:25,631 --> 01:14:29,943  X1:111 X2:610 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAnd gradually you get old and die. lt\'s\r\nimportant to make an effort sometimes.\r\n\r\n1285\r\n01:14:30,017 --> 01:14:32,254  X1:138 X2:584 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Do you think his girlfriend\'s pretty?\r\n- She\'s great looking.\r\n\r\n1286\r\n01:14:32,322 --> 01:14:35,551  X1:166 X2:555 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nA little on the androgynous side.\r\n\r\n1287\r\n01:14:35,619 --> 01:14:37,474  X1:240 X2:481 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl forgot my mantra.\r\n\r\n1288\r\n01:14:55,400 --> 01:14:57,571  X1:273 X2:448 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThat was fun.\r\n\r\n1289\r\n01:14:57,641 --> 01:15:00,641  X1:224 X2:498 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl don\'t think California\r\nis bad at all.\r\n\r\n1290\r\n01:15:00,713 --> 01:15:02,918  X1:211 X2:510 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nlt\'s a drag coming home.\r\n\r\n1291\r\n01:15:02,986 --> 01:15:06,915  X1:203 X2:518 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nA lot of beautiful women.\r\nlt was fun to flirt.\r\n\r\n1292\r\n01:15:06,987 --> 01:15:09,027  X1:233 X2:488 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl have to face facts.\r\n\r\n1293\r\n01:15:09,099 --> 01:15:13,541  X1:160 X2:561 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl adore Alvy, but our relationship\r\ndoesn\'t seem to work anymore.\r\n\r\n1294\r\n01:15:13,613 --> 01:15:17,192  X1:206 X2:516 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl\'ll have the usual trouble\r\nwith Annie in bed tonight.\r\n\r\n1295\r\n01:15:17,262 --> 01:15:19,117  X1:242 X2:479 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWhy do l need this?\r\n\r\n1296\r\n01:15:19,183 --> 01:15:23,919  X1:153 X2:568 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlf only l had the nerve to break up,\r\nbut it would really hurt him.\r\n\r\n1297\r\n01:15:23,984 --> 01:15:27,367  X1:202 X2:519 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlf only l didn\'t feel guilty\r\nasking Annie to move out.\r\n\r\n1298\r\n01:15:27,440 --> 01:15:30,670  X1:213 X2:508 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt\'d probably wreck her,\r\nbut l should be honest.\r\n\r\n1299\r\n01:15:30,737 --> 01:15:33,356  X1:253 X2:468 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAlvy, let\'s face it.\r\n\r\n1300\r\n01:15:33,426 --> 01:15:37,005  X1:192 X2:529 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl don\'t think our relationship\r\nis working.\r\n\r\n1301\r\n01:15:37,076 --> 01:15:39,978  X1:231 X2:491 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl know. A relationship\r\nis like a shark:\r\n\r\n1302\r\n01:15:40,052 --> 01:15:43,217  X1:213 X2:509 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt has to constantly\r\nmove forward or it dies.\r\n\r\n1303\r\n01:15:43,285 --> 01:15:47,083  X1:187 X2:535 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAnd l think what we\'ve got\r\non our hands is a dead shark.\r\n\r\n1304\r\n01:15:47,158 --> 01:15:49,809  X1:150 X2:572 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- Whose Catcher in the Rye is this?\r\n- lf it has my name on it...\r\n\r\n1305\r\n01:15:49,879 --> 01:15:51,952  X1:262 X2:459 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl guess it\'s mine.\r\n\r\n1306\r\n01:15:52,023 --> 01:15:57,557  X1:134 X2:588 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou wrote your name in all my books,\r\n\'cause you knew this day would come.\r\n\r\n1307\r\n01:15:57,625 --> 01:16:00,942  X1:215 X2:507 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou wanted to break up\r\njust as much as l do.\r\n\r\n1308\r\n01:16:01,018 --> 01:16:04,793  X1:182 X2:540 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo question. l think\r\nwe\'re doing the mature thing.\r\n\r\n1309\r\n01:16:04,859 --> 01:16:08,056  X1:183 X2:539 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nLook. All the books\r\non death and dying are yours.\r\n\r\n1310\r\n01:16:08,124 --> 01:16:10,459  X1:154 X2:567 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAnd all the poetry books are mine.\r\n\r\n1311\r\n01:16:10,524 --> 01:16:13,787  X1:179 X2:542 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nDenial of Death.\r\nThis is the first book l got you.\r\n\r\n1312\r\n01:16:13,853 --> 01:16:15,708  X1:230 X2:491 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nRemember that day?\r\n\r\n1313\r\n01:16:15,773 --> 01:16:18,262  X1:189 X2:532 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl feel like there\'s\r\na great weight off my back.\r\n\r\n1314\r\n01:16:19,902 --> 01:16:21,790  X1:271 X2:451 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThanks, honey.\r\n\r\n1315\r\n01:16:21,855 --> 01:16:27,007  X1:144 X2:577 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl mean, no. l think it\'s important\r\nfor us to explore new relationships.\r\n\r\n1316\r\n01:16:27,073 --> 01:16:31,962  X1:116 X2:606 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThere\'s no question about that, because\r\nwe\'ve given this a more than fair shot.\r\n\r\n1317\r\n01:16:32,034 --> 01:16:34,139  X1:193 X2:528 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nMy analyst thinks this move\r\nis key for me.\r\n\r\n1318\r\n01:16:34,210 --> 01:16:38,401  X1:124 X2:598 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAnd l trust her,\r\nbecause my analyst recommended her.\r\n\r\n1319\r\n01:16:38,468 --> 01:16:41,436  X1:138 X2:583 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhy should l put you through\r\nall my moods and hang-ups anyway?\r\n\r\n1320\r\n01:16:41,509 --> 01:16:44,892  X1:104 X2:617 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou know what the beauty part is?\r\nWe can always come back together again.\r\n\r\n1321\r\n01:16:44,966 --> 01:16:47,039  X1:233 X2:489 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- There\'s no problem.\r\n- Exactly.\r\n\r\n1322\r\n01:16:47,110 --> 01:16:51,551  X1:129 X2:593 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl don\'t think many couples could handle\r\nthis, break up and remain friends.\r\n\r\n1323\r\n01:16:51,624 --> 01:16:54,209  X1:245 X2:477 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThis button is mine.\r\nRemember?\r\n\r\n1324\r\n01:16:54,280 --> 01:16:57,859  X1:118 X2:603 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThese are yours. \"lmpeach Eisenhower.\"\r\n\"lmpeach Nixon.\"\r\n\r\n1325\r\n01:16:57,929 --> 01:17:01,411  X1:197 X2:524 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n\"lmpeach Lyndon Johnson.\"\r\n\"lmpeach Ronald Reagan.\"\r\n\r\n1326\r\n01:17:02,826 --> 01:17:06,176  X1:206 X2:516 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl miss Annie.\r\nl made a terrible mistake.\r\n\r\n1327\r\n01:17:06,251 --> 01:17:09,154  X1:204 X2:517 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nShe\'s living in Los Angeles\r\nwith Tony Lacey.\r\n\r\n1328\r\n01:17:09,228 --> 01:17:12,644  X1:146 X2:575 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlf she is, then the hell with her. lf\r\nshe likes that lifestyle, let her stay.\r\n\r\n1329\r\n01:17:12,716 --> 01:17:15,467  X1:204 X2:518 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- He\'s a jerk for one thing.\r\n- He graduated Harvard.\r\n\r\n1330\r\n01:17:15,534 --> 01:17:19,277  X1:177 X2:545 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nHarvard makes mistakes, too.\r\nKissinger taught there.\r\n\r\n1331\r\n01:17:20,207 --> 01:17:22,509  X1:188 X2:533 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nDon\'t tell me you\'re jealous?\r\n\r\n1332\r\n01:17:22,576 --> 01:17:24,616  X1:202 X2:520 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYeah. Jealous? A little bit.\r\nLike Medea.\r\n\r\n1333\r\n01:17:24,688 --> 01:17:28,203  X1:184 X2:537 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nCan l show you something?\r\nl found this in the apartment.\r\n\r\n1334\r\n01:17:28,274 --> 01:17:32,879  X1:128 X2:594 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nBlack soap. She used to wash her face\r\n800 times a day with black soap.\r\n\r\n1335\r\n01:17:32,947 --> 01:17:34,856  X1:252 X2:470 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nDon\'t ask me why.\r\n\r\n1336\r\n01:17:34,931 --> 01:17:37,354  X1:114 X2:607 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWhy don\'t you go out with other women?\r\n\r\n1337\r\n01:17:37,428 --> 01:17:40,561  X1:213 X2:508 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl tried,\r\nbut it\'s very depressing.\r\n\r\n1338\r\n01:17:40,628 --> 01:17:43,444  X1:193 X2:528 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThis always happens to me.\r\nQuick! Get a broom!\r\n\r\n1339\r\n01:17:43,509 --> 01:17:46,543  X1:225 X2:497 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat are you making\r\nsuch a big deal about?\r\n\r\n1340\r\n01:17:46,615 --> 01:17:49,201  X1:230 X2:492 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThey\'re only lobsters.\r\n\r\n1341\r\n01:17:49,271 --> 01:17:52,436  X1:125 X2:597 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n-You\'re adult. You can pick up lobsters.\r\n-l\'m not myself since l quit smoking.\r\n\r\n1342\r\n01:17:52,503 --> 01:17:55,636  X1:239 X2:483 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- When did you quit?\r\n- Sixteen years ago.\r\n\r\n1343\r\n01:17:55,705 --> 01:17:58,422  X1:233 X2:489 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- What do you mean?\r\n- Mean?\r\n\r\n1344\r\n01:18:01,51 --> 01:18:02,362  X1:145 X2:577 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou stopped smoking 16 years ago.\r\nls that what you said?\r\n\r\n1345\r\n01:18:04,155 --> 01:18:06,392  X1:247 X2:474 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl don\'t understand.\r\n\r\n1346\r\n01:18:06,459 --> 01:18:08,981  X1:213 X2:508 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAre you joking or what?\r\n\r\n1347\r\n01:18:19,807 --> 01:18:21,913  X1:183 X2:538 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nCentral Park\'s turning green.\r\n\r\n1348\r\n01:18:21,984 --> 01:18:26,655  X1:162 X2:559 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl saw that lunatic we used to see\r\nwith the pinwheel hat...\r\n\r\n1349\r\n01:18:26,721 --> 01:18:29,023  X1:228 X2:494 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nand the roller-skates.\r\n\r\n1350\r\n01:18:29,089 --> 01:18:32,407  X1:138 X2:584 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nListen, l want you to come back here.\r\n\r\n1351\r\n01:18:32,482 --> 01:18:35,745  X1:134 X2:587 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWell, then l\'m going to come out there\r\nand get you.\r\n\r\n1352\r\n01:18:39,941 --> 01:18:42,146  X1:169 X2:553 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat do you mean, where am l?\r\nWhere do you think l am?\r\n\r\n1353\r\n01:18:42,213 --> 01:18:46,241  X1:177 X2:545 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl\'m at the Los Angeles airport.\r\nl flew in.\r\n\r\n1354\r\n01:18:46,311 --> 01:18:49,028  X1:246 X2:476 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl flew in to see you.\r\n\r\n1355\r\n01:18:49,095 --> 01:18:52,194  X1:219 X2:502 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nCan we not debate this\r\non the telephone...\r\n\r\n1356\r\n01:18:52,264 --> 01:18:54,982  X1:158 X2:563 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nbecause l\'ve got a temperature...\r\n\r\n1357\r\n01:18:55,049 --> 01:18:58,955  X1:199 X2:522 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nand l\'m getting my chronic\r\nLos Angeles nausea again.\r\n\r\n1358\r\n01:18:59,084 --> 01:19:01,418  X1:184 X2:537 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWherever you want to meet.\r\nl don\'t care.\r\n\r\n1359\r\n01:19:01,484 --> 01:19:03,372  X1:273 X2:448 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl\'ll drive in.\r\nl rented a car.\r\n\r\n1360\r\n01:19:04,493 --> 01:19:06,349  X1:293 X2:429 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl\'m driving.\r\n\r\n1361\r\n01:19:06,414 --> 01:19:09,229  X1:181 X2:540 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat, is that such a miracle?\r\nl\'m driving myself.\r\n\r\n1362\r\n01:19:24,851 --> 01:19:27,601  X1:129 X2:593 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl\'m going to have the alfalfa sprouts...\r\n\r\n1363\r\n01:19:27,667 --> 01:19:31,181  X1:183 X2:538 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nand a plate of mashed yeast.\r\n\r\n1364\r\n01:19:49,945 --> 01:19:51,538  X1:263 X2:459 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYou look pretty.\r\n\r\n1365\r\n01:19:51,609 --> 01:19:55,091  X1:191 X2:531 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo, l just lost a little weight,\r\nthat\'s all.\r\n\r\n1366\r\n01:19:59,324 --> 01:20:02,074  X1:249 X2:472 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWell, you look nice.\r\n\r\n1367\r\n01:20:02,141 --> 01:20:05,818  X1:183 X2:538 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl think we should get married.\r\n\r\n1368\r\n01:20:05,886 --> 01:20:07,293  X1:304 X2:417 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nCome on.\r\n\r\n1369\r\n01:20:09,054 --> 01:20:13,333  X1:170 X2:551 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhy, you want to live out here?\r\nlt\'s like living in Munchkinland.\r\n\r\n1370\r\n01:20:13,408 --> 01:20:17,020  X1:196 X2:526 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat do you mean?\r\nlt\'s perfectly fine out here.\r\n\r\n1371\r\n01:20:17,088 --> 01:20:20,351  X1:260 X2:462 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nTony\'s very nice.\r\n\r\n1372\r\n01:20:20,417 --> 01:20:23,484  X1:193 X2:529 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl meet people, go to parties\r\nand play tennis.\r\n\r\n1373\r\n01:20:23,554 --> 01:20:26,206  X1:181 X2:541 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThat\'s a very big step for me.\r\n\r\n1374\r\n01:20:26,275 --> 01:20:29,276  X1:180 X2:541 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl\'m able to enjoy people more.\r\n\r\n1375\r\n01:20:29,348 --> 01:20:32,219  X1:177 X2:544 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re not going to come back\r\nto New York?\r\n\r\n1376\r\n01:20:32,293 --> 01:20:36,037  X1:121 X2:601 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat\'s so great about New York? lt\'s a\r\ndying city. You read Death in Venice.\r\n\r\n1377\r\n01:20:36,102 --> 01:20:39,299  X1:172 X2:549 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou didn\'t read Death in Venice\r\nuntil l bought it for you.\r\n\r\n1378\r\n01:20:39,367 --> 01:20:42,630  X1:139 X2:583 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThat\'s right. You only gave me books\r\nwith the word \"death\" in the title.\r\n\r\n1379\r\n01:20:42,696 --> 01:20:44,966  X1:167 X2:555 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nBecause it\'s an important issue.\r\n\r\n1380\r\n01:20:45,032 --> 01:20:47,902  X1:161 X2:561 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re incapable of enjoying life.\r\nYou know that?\r\n\r\n1381\r\n01:20:47,977 --> 01:20:50,312  X1:204 X2:518 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re like New York City.\r\nYou\'re just this person.\r\n\r\n1382\r\n01:20:50,378 --> 01:20:52,866  X1:146 X2:576 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYou\'re like this island unto yourself.\r\n\r\n1383\r\n01:20:52,938 --> 01:20:55,906  X1:231 X2:490 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl can\'t enjoy anything\r\nunless everybody is.\r\n\r\n1384\r\n01:20:55,979 --> 01:21:00,170  X1:161 X2:561 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlf one guy is starving someplace,\r\nit puts a crimp in my evening.\r\n\r\n1385\r\n01:21:02,509 --> 01:21:04,364  X1:185 X2:536 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nDo you want to get married?\r\n\r\n1386\r\n01:21:06,382 --> 01:21:09,416  X1:251 X2:470 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nNo. We\'re friends.\r\n\r\n1387\r\n01:21:09,487 --> 01:21:12,074  X1:211 X2:511 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl want to remain friends.\r\n\r\n1388\r\n01:21:14,064 --> 01:21:15,438  X1:275 X2:446 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nCheck please.\r\n\r\n1389\r\n01:21:15,505 --> 01:21:18,375  X1:215 X2:507 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYou\'re mad, aren\'t you?\r\n\r\n1390\r\n01:21:18,449 --> 01:21:21,200  X1:159 X2:562 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYes, of course l\'m mad,\r\nbecause you love me. l know that.\r\n\r\n1391\r\n01:21:21,267 --> 01:21:23,688  X1:201 X2:521 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl can\'t say that that\'s true\r\nat this point in my life.\r\n\r\n1392\r\n01:21:23,763 --> 01:21:26,381  X1:190 X2:531 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl really can\'t say that\'s true.\r\n\r\n1393\r\n01:21:26,451 --> 01:21:29,234  X1:156 X2:565 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nYou know how wonderful you are.\r\n\r\n1394\r\n01:21:29,301 --> 01:21:33,011  X1:123 X2:598 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re the reason l got out of my room,\r\nthat l was able to sing...\r\n\r\n1395\r\n01:21:33,078 --> 01:21:37,235  X1:127 X2:595 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nand get more in touch with my feelings\r\nand all that crap.\r\n\r\n1396\r\n01:21:37,302 --> 01:21:39,604  X1:280 X2:442 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nListen, listen.\r\n\r\n1397\r\n01:21:40,824 --> 01:21:42,482  X1:220 X2:502 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nSo what are you up to?\r\n\r\n1398\r\n01:21:44,792 --> 01:21:48,568  X1:186 X2:536 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThe usual. l\'m trying to write.\r\nl\'m working on a play.\r\n\r\n1399\r\n01:21:50,330 --> 01:21:52,818  X1:128 X2:593 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAre you saying you\'re not coming back\r\nto New York with me?\r\n\r\n1400\r\n01:21:54,075 --> 01:21:58,647  X1:298 X2:424 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nNo. Look.\r\nl gotta go.\r\n\r\n1401\r\n01:21:58,717 --> 01:22:01,946  X1:184 X2:537 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat do you mean?\r\nl flew 3,000 miles to see you.\r\n\r\n1402\r\n01:22:02,013 --> 01:22:04,664  X1:165 X2:556 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAir miles. Do you know\r\nwhat that does to my stomach?\r\n\r\n1403\r\n01:22:04,733 --> 01:22:06,643  X1:202 X2:519 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlf you must know,\r\nit\'s a hectic time for Tony.\r\n\r\n1404\r\n01:22:06,718 --> 01:22:08,628  X1:193 X2:528 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- The Grammys are tonight.\r\n- The what?\r\n\r\n1405\r\n01:22:08,703 --> 01:22:10,744  X1:191 X2:531 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThe Grammys. He\'s got a lot\r\nof records up for awards.\r\n\r\n1406\r\n01:22:10,815 --> 01:22:13,402  X1:153 X2:568 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThey give awards for that music?\r\nl thought just ear plugs.\r\n\r\n1407\r\n01:22:13,473 --> 01:22:16,889  X1:208 X2:513 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nJust forget it. Let\'s just\r\nforget the conversation.\r\n\r\n1408\r\n01:22:16,961 --> 01:22:19,930  X1:137 X2:584 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThey do nothing but give out awards.\r\nl can\'t believe it.\r\n\r\n1409\r\n01:22:20,001 --> 01:22:23,068  X1:197 X2:524 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nGreatest Fascist Dictator:\r\nAdolph Hitler.\r\n\r\n1410\r\n01:22:52,075 --> 01:22:54,825  X1:167 X2:554 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl know what you\'re going to say.\r\nl\'m not a great driver.\r\n\r\n1411\r\n01:22:54,892 --> 01:22:57,925  X1:167 X2:555 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- l have some problems with--\r\n- May l see your license, please?\r\n\r\n1412\r\n01:22:57,997 --> 01:23:00,485  X1:234 X2:488 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nJust don\'t get angry.\r\n\r\n1413\r\n01:23:00,557 --> 01:23:04,268  X1:226 X2:496 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl have my license here.\r\nlt\'s a rented car.\r\n\r\n1414\r\n01:23:06,158 --> 01:23:09,355  X1:176 X2:545 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nDon\'t give me your life\'s story.\r\n\r\n1415\r\n01:23:09,423 --> 01:23:11,594  X1:217 X2:504 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nJust pick up the license.\r\n\r\n1416\r\n01:23:11,664 --> 01:23:15,374  X1:146 X2:575 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou have to ask nicely, because\r\nl\'ve had a rough day. My girlfriend--\r\n\r\n1417\r\n01:23:15,440 --> 01:23:17,808  X1:166 X2:556 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nJust give me the license, please.\r\n\r\n1418\r\n01:23:19,506 --> 01:23:22,190  X1:202 X2:519 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nSince you put it that way,\r\nit\'s hard for me to refuse.\r\n\r\n1419\r\n01:23:22,259 --> 01:23:25,227  X1:213 X2:509 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl have a terrific problem\r\nwith authority.\r\n\r\n1420\r\n01:23:25,299 --> 01:23:27,602  X1:226 X2:496 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt\'s not your fault.\r\nDon\'t take it personal.\r\n\r\n1421\r\n01:23:35,478 --> 01:23:37,934  X1:261 X2:460 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nSo long, fellows.\r\nKeep in touch.\r\n\r\n1422\r\n01:23:47,065 --> 01:23:50,744  X1:238 X2:484 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlmagine my surprise\r\nwhen l got your call.\r\n\r\n1423\r\n01:23:50,811 --> 01:23:53,911  X1:201 X2:521 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYeah. l had the feeling\r\nl got you at a bad moment.\r\n\r\n1424\r\n01:23:53,979 --> 01:23:56,184  X1:175 X2:546 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl heard high-pitched squealing.\r\n\r\n1425\r\n01:23:56,252 --> 01:23:57,659  X1:290 X2:432 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nTwins, Max.\r\n\r\n1426\r\n01:23:58,525 --> 01:24:00,500  X1:246 X2:475 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nSixteen-year-olds.\r\n\r\n1427\r\n01:24:01,949 --> 01:24:05,528  X1:150 X2:571 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nCan you imagine the mathematical\r\npossibilities of that?\r\n\r\n1428\r\n01:24:05,599 --> 01:24:08,948  X1:142 X2:580 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re an actor. You should be doing\r\nShakespeare in the park.\r\n\r\n1429\r\n01:24:09,023 --> 01:24:12,221  X1:182 X2:539 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl did Shakespeare in the park.\r\nl got mugged.\r\n\r\n1430\r\n01:24:12,289 --> 01:24:15,551  X1:130 X2:591 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl was playing Richard ll. Two guys\r\nwith leather jackets stole my leotard.\r\n\r\n1431\r\n01:24:20,898 --> 01:24:24,063  X1:149 X2:572 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAre we driving through plutonium?\r\n\r\n1432\r\n01:24:24,131 --> 01:24:27,448  X1:204 X2:517 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nKeeps out the alpha rays.\r\nYou don\'t get old.\r\n\r\n1433\r\n01:24:29,636 --> 01:24:32,834  X1:151 X2:570 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re a thinking person.\r\nHow can you choose this lifestyle?\r\n\r\n1434\r\n01:24:32,902 --> 01:24:35,521  X1:150 X2:571 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nWhat is so great about New York?\r\n\r\n1435\r\n01:24:35,591 --> 01:24:38,658  X1:206 X2:516 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt\'s a dying city.\r\nYou read Death in Venice.\r\n\r\n1436\r\n01:24:38,727 --> 01:24:41,029  X1:172 X2:549 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou didn\'t read Death in Venice\r\nuntil l gave it to you.\r\n\r\n1437\r\n01:24:41,097 --> 01:24:43,333  X1:160 X2:561 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou only give me books\r\nwith the word \"death\" in the title.\r\n\r\n1438\r\n01:24:43,400 --> 01:24:47,144  X1:153 X2:569 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\n- lt\'s an important issue.\r\n- You\'re incapable of enjoying life.\r\n\r\n1439\r\n01:24:47,210 --> 01:24:50,178  X1:232 X2:490 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou\'re like New York.\r\nYou\'re an island.\r\n\r\n1440\r\n01:24:50,250 --> 01:24:53,731  X1:156 X2:565 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nOkay. lf that\'s all that we\'ve been\r\nthrough together means to you...\r\n\r\n1441\r\n01:24:53,803 --> 01:24:57,317  X1:145 X2:577 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nit\'s better if we just said good-bye,\r\nonce and for all.\r\n\r\n1442\r\n01:24:57,388 --> 01:24:58,850  X1:300 X2:421 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nlt\'s funny.\r\n\r\n1443\r\n01:24:58,925 --> 01:25:01,227  X1:197 X2:524 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAfter all the serious talks\r\nand passionate moments...\r\n\r\n1444\r\n01:25:01,293 --> 01:25:04,677  X1:160 X2:562 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nthat it ends here, in a health food\r\nrestaurant on Sunset Boulevard.\r\n\r\n1445\r\n01:25:05,422 --> 01:25:07,725  X1:262 X2:459 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nGood-bye, Sally.\r\n\r\n1446\r\n01:25:07,791 --> 01:25:12,047  X1:216 X2:505 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWait.\r\nl\'m going to go with you.\r\n\r\n1447\r\n01:25:12,113 --> 01:25:14,000  X1:302 X2:420 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl love you.\r\n\r\n1448\r\n01:25:17,266 --> 01:25:20,049  X1:239 X2:483 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhat do you want?\r\nlt was my first play.\r\n\r\n1449\r\n01:25:20,115 --> 01:25:23,050  X1:128 X2:594 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nYou know how you\'re always trying to\r\nget things to come out perfect in art...\r\n\r\n1450\r\n01:25:23,124 --> 01:25:26,223  X1:168 X2:553 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nbecause it\'s real difficult in life.\r\n\r\n1451\r\n01:25:26,292 --> 01:25:30,668  X1:211 X2:510 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlnterestingly, however,\r\nl did run into Annie again.\r\n\r\n1452\r\n01:25:30,741 --> 01:25:32,716  X1:179 X2:543 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nlt was on the Upper West Side\r\nof Manhattan.\r\n\r\n1453\r\n01:25:32,790 --> 01:25:36,369  X1:135 X2:587 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nShe had moved back to New York.\r\nShe was living in Soho with some guy.\r\n\r\n1454\r\n01:25:36,439 --> 01:25:40,368  X1:131 X2:591 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWhen l met her, she was dragging him\r\nin to see The Sorrow and the Pity...\r\n\r\n1455\r\n01:25:40,439 --> 01:25:42,928  X1:222 X2:500 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nwhich l counted\r\nas a personal triumph.\r\n\r\n1456\r\n01:25:43,001 --> 01:25:45,652  X1:221 X2:500 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAnnie and l had lunch\r\nsometime after that...\r\n\r\n1457\r\n01:25:45,721 --> 01:25:49,585  X1:160 X2:562 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nand just kicked around old times.\r\n\r\n1458\r\n01:25:49,658 --> 01:25:53,621  X1:229 X2:492 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nJust to have my arms\r\n\r\n1459\r\n01:25:55,612 --> 01:25:57,554  X1:291 X2:431 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAround you\r\n\r\n1460\r\n01:26:01,054 --> 01:26:04,438  X1:283 X2:438 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nStill the thrill\r\n\r\n1461\r\n01:26:05,022 --> 01:26:08,155  X1:243 X2:479 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nThat it was the day\r\n\r\n1462\r\n01:26:08,224 --> 01:26:10,429  X1:294 X2:427 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nl found you\r\n\r\n1463\r\n01:26:11,296 --> 01:26:14,429  X1:296 X2:426 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nSeems like\r\n\r\n1464\r\n01:26:16,577 --> 01:26:21,150  X1:303 X2:419 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nOld times\r\n\r\n1465\r\n01:26:23,651 --> 01:26:28,835  X1:206 X2:516 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nDinner dates and flowers\r\n\r\n1466\r\n01:26:31,558 --> 01:26:33,500  X1:303 X2:419 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nOld times\r\n\r\n1467\r\n01:26:34,886 --> 01:26:37,637  X1:221 X2:500 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nAfter that, it got late\r\nand we both had to go.\r\n\r\n1468\r\n01:26:37,703 --> 01:26:39,809  X1:139 X2:582 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nBut it was great seeing Annie again.\r\n\r\n1469\r\n01:26:39,880 --> 01:26:42,499  X1:160 X2:562 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nl realize\r\nwhat a terrific person she was...\r\n\r\n1470\r\n01:26:42,569 --> 01:26:45,319  X1:209 X2:513 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nand how much fun it was\r\njust knowing her.\r\n\r\n1471\r\n01:26:45,385 --> 01:26:48,899  X1:177 X2:545 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nAnd l thought of that old joke.\r\n\r\n1472\r\n01:26:48,970 --> 01:26:53,608  X1:144 X2:577 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThis guy goes to a psychiatrist\r\nand says, \"Doc, my brother\'s crazy.\r\n\r\n1473\r\n01:26:53,676 --> 01:26:56,164  X1:209 X2:513 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nHe thinks he\'s a chicken.\"\r\n\r\n1474\r\n01:26:56,237 --> 01:26:58,441  X1:191 X2:531 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThe doctor says,\r\n\"Why don\'t you turn him in?\"\r\n\r\n1475\r\n01:26:58,509 --> 01:27:01,445  X1:183 X2:539 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThe guy says,\r\n\"l would, but l need the eggs.\"\r\n\r\n1476\r\n01:27:01,518 --> 01:27:05,894  X1:148 X2:573 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nWell, l guess that\'s, now, how l feel\r\nabout relationships.\r\n\r\n1477\r\n01:27:05,967 --> 01:27:10,791  X1:205 X2:517 Y1:334 Y2:409\r\nThey\'re totally irrational,\r\ncrazy and absurd.\r\n\r\n1478\r\n01:27:10,864 --> 01:27:13,734  X1:131 X2:591 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nBut l guess we keep going through it...\r\n\r\n1479\r\n01:27:13,809 --> 01:27:16,876  X1:147 X2:574 Y1:374 Y2:410\r\nbecause most of us need the eggs.\r\n\r\n1480\r\n01:27:17,000 --> 01:27:20,067\r\nBest watched using Open Subtitles MKV Player\r\n";
            var subtitleCreator = new SubtitleCreator();

